<para>
  <classname>TimeStepper</classname> objects describe ways of taking a
  single time step when <link
  linkend="Section-Concepts-Mesh-Solving">solving</link> a time
  dependent problem.  Given a set of &field; values at time
  <inlineequation><alt role="tex">\(t\)</alt></inlineequation>, they
  compute a set of new values at time <inlineequation><alt
  role="tex">\(t+\Delta t\)</alt></inlineequation>. 
</para>
<para>
  <classname>TimeStepper</classname> is used for the
  <varname>stepper</varname> parameter for <xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-UniformDriver"/> and the
  <varname>singlestep</varname> parameter for <xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-QCTimeStepper"/>, which is used for <link
  linkend="RegisteredClass-AdaptiveDriver">adaptive</link> stepping.
</para>
<para>
  All of the time steppers in &oof2; work with both linear and <link
  linkend="Section-Concepts-Mesh-Equation-Nonlinear">nonlinear</link>
  equations.
</para>

